title: 'PITFALL: The & can be omitted from pointer receivers.'
pid: b1eb1cbc-1961-4a2c-8667-1f85740c9223
body: |2-
  but not for regular functions.
  That is, if the following type signatures apply:
    func f (*Vertex)
    func (*Vertex) m
    var v Vertex
  then
    f(&v)    // works
    f(v)     // does not work
    (&v).m() // works
    v.m()    // works, due to shorthand
